@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Introduction@{ub}



Tool Type Editor is a utility program to quickly and easily edit Tool
Types in icon files.


A full collection of tools is supplied to make short work for updates
and changes.


@ENDNODE


@NODE UsingProgram "Using Tool Type Editor"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Using Tool Type Editor@{ub}



@{"  " LINK StartingProg} Starting Tool Type Editor


@{"  " LINK MenuStrip} Menu Strip


@{"  " LINK MainEditor} Main Editor


@ENDNODE


@NODE StartingProg "Starting Tool Type Editor"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Starting Tool Type Editor@{ub}



This program may be started from the Workbench or the Shell window.


This program will detach from the Shell so you need not use Run or any other
variant.  There are a few command line arguments you may use when loading:



@{b}FILE/K@{ub}

File to edit without the .info extension.


@{b}ICONIFY/S@{ub}

Start in iconified mode.


@{b}ICON_X/K@{ub}

X coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}ICON_Y/K@{ub}

Y coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}

Name of public screen to open the interface on.


@{b}LANGUAGE/K@{ub}

Preferred locale strings language.

Language must be all lower case.


@{b}DONOTDETACH/S@{ub}

Do not detach from the Shell.



The arguments are not case sensitive and may be mixed in any order.

ex: ToolTypeEditor FILE MyProgram ICONIFY


@ENDNODE


@NODE MenuStrip "Menu Strip"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Menu Strip@{ub}



@{b}Project@{ub}


@{b}Iconify@{ub}

Iconify the program and place an AppIcon on the default public screen.


@{b}About...@{ub}

Will open a large requester with some pertinent information about the
program.


@{b}Quit@{ub}

Will terminate the program.



@{b}Type@{ub}


@{b}Volume@{ub}

Change icon type to Volume.


@{b}Drawer@{ub}

Change icon type to Drawer.


@{b}Tool@{ub}

Change icon type to Tool.


@{b}Project@{ub}

Change icon type to Project.


@{b}Trashcan@{ub}

Change icon type to Trashcan.



@{b}Tool Types@{ub}


@{b}Disable All@{ub}

Disable all tool types.


@{b}Enable All@{ub}

Enable all tool types.


@{b}Toggle All@{ub}

Toggle disable/enable of all tool types.



@{b}Clipboard@{ub}


@{b}Cut@{ub}

Cut tooltype and replace the clipboard.


@{b}Copy@{ub}

Copy tooltype and replace the clipboard.


@{b}Cut And Append@{ub}

Cut tooltype and append it to the end of the clipboard.


@{b}Copy And Append@{ub}

Copy tooltype and append it to the end of the clipboard.


@{b}Paste@{ub}

Paste the clipboard contents after the current node.


@ENDNODE


@NODE MainEditor "Main Editor"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Main Editor@{ub}



@{b}Information Box@{ub}

Displays information about the icon being editted.


@{b}Stack@{ub}

Stack size for program.


@{b}Comment@{ub}

Comment for file.


@{b}Default Tool@{ub}

Project's default tool.  A file picker is available to change tools.


@{b}Tool Types@{ub}

List of Tool Types.


@{b}Tool Type@{ub}

Selected Tool Type to be editted.


@{b}Top@{ub}

Move selected Tool Type to the top of the list.


@{b}Up@{ub}

Move selected Tool Type up one position.


@{b}Down@{ub}

Move selected Tool Type down one position.


@{b}Bottom@{ub}

Move selected Tool Type to the bottom of the list.


@{b}Sort@{ub}

Alphabetize list.


@{b}Script@{ub}

Set or clear Script protection bit.


@{b}Pure@{ub}

Set or clear Pure protection bit.


@{b}Archive@{ub}

Set or clear Archive protection bit.


@{b}Read@{ub}

Set or clear Read protection bit.


@{b}Write@{ub}

Set or clear Write protection bit.


@{b}Execute@{ub}

Set or clear Execute protection bit.


@{b}Delete@{ub}

Set or clear Delete protection bit.


@{b}New@{ub}

Append a new Tool Type to end of the list.


@{b}Toggle@{ub}

Toggle current tool type disabled/enabled.


@{b}Insert@{ub}

Insert a new Tool Type before the selected Tool Type.


@{b}Copy@{ub}

Copy the selected Tool Type and place at end of the list.


@{b}Remove@{ub}

Remove the selected Tool Type.


@{b}Open@{ub}

Select a different icon to edit.


@{b}Load@{ub}

Re-load icon's Tool Types.


@{b}Save@{ub}

Save Tool Types to icon.


@{b}Quit@{ub}

This will terminate the program.


@ENDNODE


@NODE GadTools "GadTools"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}GadTools@{ub}



Thanks to Olaf `Olsen' Barthel, author of gtlayout.library.  It is by far
the best user interface package.  Also thanks for all his programming help.


The user interface is totally font and screen mode sensitive.  All
gadgets and the window will automatically adjust to match your preferences.


The latest features are utilized to get the most from the operating
system and to make the program the best of it's kind.


@ENDNODE


@NODE LocaleSupport "Locale Support"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Locale Support@{ub}



This is program is totally localized to allow support for foreign
languages.  A catalog may not be available for your language at this time,
but one will hopefully be available soon.


If you are willing to translate the strings to another language, please let
me know.  If you do offer, a perfect translation of all strings will be
expected.  It is all or nothing.  I will also be seeking your assistance for
future versions that have new strings.


@ENDNODE


@NODE OperationNotes "Operation Notes"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Operation Notes@{ub}



Press the Help key for AmigaGuide help.


It can be started in WBStartup and iconified so it is always available.


The icon file will not have it's Execute flag set.  ex: ----RW-D


